items.title: Autonomous Bipedal Robot Can Change Its Own Batteries, Work 24/7
items.description: Move over, humans. This latest, the Walker S2, just made your 9-to-5 look prehistoric. The humanoid robot doesn’t just walk on two legs like the rest of us, it swaps its own batteries and keeps chugging along 24/7 without so much as a coffee break. Built by UB Tech Robotics, this silicon super worker toddles over to a battery swap station when its juice runs low, yanks out the dead cell with its robo-hands, slaps in a fresh one, and goes right back to work. No union, no sick days, no small talk. Inspired by China’s modular electric car batteries, the whole process takes just minutes. The kicker? It’s designed for industrial use. SMH

items.title: Popular Aquarium Fish Has Been Thriving in Ukraine’s Polluted Sewers for Decades
items.description: Turns out Ukraine’s sewers are the hottest real estate for tropical fish, specifically guppies from South America who’ve been partying in Kyiv’s polluted wastewater since the 1980s. That’s right, while your houseplants are wilting and your goldfish lasted a week, these guppies are thriving in stinky sludge and breeding like it’s spring break. Scientists confirm they’re chilling in a sewage treatment plant, dodging toxic sludge like champs, proving once again that nature laughs in the face of human messes. Meanwhile, you’re still using a Brita filter for your tap water. SMH.
